Draws a closed polygon defined by arrays of <i>x</i> and <i>y</i> coordinates. Each pair of (<i>x</i>,&nbsp;<i>y</i>) coordinates defines a point. <p> This method draws the polygon defined by <code>nPoint</code> line segments, where the first <code>nPoint&nbsp;-&nbsp;1</code> line segments are line segments from <code>(xPoints[i&nbsp;-&nbsp;1],&nbsp;yPoints[i&nbsp;-&nbsp;1])</code> to <code>(xPoints[i],&nbsp;yPoints[i])</code>, for 1&nbsp;&le;&nbsp;<i>i</i>&nbsp;&le;&nbsp;<code>nPoints</code>. The figure is automatically closed by drawing a line connecting the final point to the first point, if those points are different.
